                        <br/><br/><br/><h2>文 献</h2><br><ol><br><li id="R1"><span class='au'>Kai, M., Furuya, K., Paderi, F. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Rad3-dependent phosphorylation of the checkpoint clamp regulates repair-pathway choice.</span> <span class='so'>Nat. Cell Biol., 9, 691-697 (2007)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17515930" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R2"><span class='au'>Zou, L. & Elledge, S. J.</span>: <span class="ti">Sensing DNA damage through ATRIP recognition of RPA-ssDNA complexes.</span> <span class='so'>Science, 300, 1542-1548 (2003)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12791985" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R3"><span class='au'>Xu, X., Vaithiyalingam, S., Glick, G. G. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">The basic cleft of RPA70N binds multiple checkpoint proteins, including RAD9, to regulate ATR signaling.</span> <span class='so'>Mol. Cell. Biol., 28, 7345-7353 (2008)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18936170" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R4"><span class='au'>Bochkareva, E., Kaustov, L., Ayed, A. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Single-stranded DNA mimicry in the p53 transactivation domain interaction with replication protein A.</span> <span class='so'>Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, 102, 15412-15417 (2005)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16234232" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R5"><span class='au'>Delacroix, S., Wagner, J. M., Kobayashi, M. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">The Rad9-Hus1-Rad1 (9-1-1) clamp activates checkpoint signaling via TopBP1.</span> <span class='so'>Genes Dev., 21, 1472-1477 (2007)[<a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17575048" target="_blank">PubMed</a>]</span></li><br><li id="R6"><span class='au'>Takeishi, Y., Ohashi, E., Ogawa, K. et al.</span>: <span class="ti">Casein kinase 2-dependent phosphorylation of human Rad9 mediates the interaction between human Rad9-Hus1-Rad1 complex and TopBP